  "text": "Meta-analysis was performed by using RevMan software (version 5.3, the Cochrane Collaboration, Copenhagen, Denmark). Subgroup analyzes were performed to identify important clinical characters, and all the analyzes were first performed based on clinical homogeneity. After that, χ [CITATION_1] and I 2 statistical tests were used to judge and present the statistical heterogeneity across the trials. A homogeneity was considered when I 2 50%, and fixed-effects model was chosen. Random-effects model was chosen when a heterogeneity existed, I 2 .50%. Risk ratio (RR) and mean difference with their respective 95% confidence intervals (CIs) were presented for pooled effect size. Invested funnel plots were used to assess the risks of publication bias.",
